description.narrative: In 2019 the justice system in Iraq became more child-friendly and in line with international standards, with more children in conflict with the law diverted from the formal system, while those who end up in the formal system access legal assistance and given alternative to detention leading to overall reduction in number of children in pre and post-trial detention. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:26/12/2018
